    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 10,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 11,
      "text": "This is to advise the Bureau that on June 25, 1950, [REDACTED]",
      "status": "redaction_marker_check"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 12,
      "text": "[REDACTED], N.W., telephone, [REDACTED] and who is",
      "status": "redaction_marker_check"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 13,
      "text": "employed at the Hot Shoppe, Connecticut Avenue, N.W., informed that at",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 14,
      "text": "9:25 am, that date, while looking out of the window of his residence he",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 15,
      "text": "saw what he believed to be a flying saucer. He described this object as",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 16,
      "text": "resembling a cigar, the end of which was tilted down toward the earth",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 17,
      "text": "and presenting a silver appearance. He estimated the height of this ob-",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 18,
      "text": "ject as from 20 to 25 thousand feet, and stated the size at that distance",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 19,
      "text": "appeared to be about four inches. [REDACTED] could furnish no further de-",
      "status": "redaction_marker_check"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 20,
      "text": "tails other than to state the object appeared to be moving in an easterly",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 21,
      "text": "direction. He advised that this is the first flying saucer he has ever",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 22,
      "text": "seen.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 23,
      "status": "blank"
    },
